(774, 'Capillary leak syndrome', '', 'Vascular disorders', 'A disorder characterized by leakage of intravascular fluids into the extravascular space. This syndrome is observed in patients who demonstrate a state of generalized leaky capillaries following shock syndromes, low-flow states, ischemia-reperfusion injuries, toxemias, medications, or poisoning.  It can lead to generalized edema and multiple organ failure.', 'Please rate the following on a scale from 1 to 5: Capillary leak syndrome', '', 1, 1, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
